## `not-found.tsx` — implementation rules

- **Renders inside the parent layout** — no need to reconstruct the shell. The sidebar, topbar, and shell context remain mounted.
- **Cannot receive `params` as props.** To access dynamic segments (e.g. `orgSlug`), use a Client Component with `useParams()` from `next/navigation`.
- **Can be a Server Component** using `headers()` / `getRequestAppLocale()` for locale-aware content when no dynamic params are needed.
- For **dashboard** and **admin** surfaces (where `orgSlug` enables contextual recovery links), use a Client Component.
- For **operator** and routes without dynamic params, a Server Component suffices.
- When the surface has a per-page shell (e.g. `PlatformAdminShell` in operator pages), the `not-found.tsx` should wrap content in that same shell for continuity.

```tsx
// dashboard/not-found.tsx — Client Component for orgSlug access
"use client"
import { useParams } from "next/navigation"
import { Link } from "#i18n/navigation"

export default function OrgDashboardNotFound() {
  const params = useParams<{ orgSlug: string }>()
  return (
    <div className="flex min-h-[40vh] flex-col items-center justify-center gap-4 p-6 text-center">
      <p className="text-sm font-medium text-muted-foreground">404</p>
      <h1 className="text-lg font-medium text-foreground">Page not found</h1>
      <p className="max-w-md text-sm text-muted-foreground">
        The dashboard shell is still available — use the sidebar to navigate.
      </p>
      {params?.orgSlug ? (
        <Link href={`/o/${params.orgSlug}/dashboard`}>Back to dashboard</Link>
      ) : null}
    </div>
  )
}
```

### HTTP status and streaming

`notFound()` called in a **layout** (before any `await` or Suspense boundary) returns true **HTTP 404**.

`notFound()` called in a **page** behind a `loading.tsx` Suspense boundary returns **HTTP 200** (the response is already streaming) with not-found UI rendered.

For **private authenticated surfaces** (dashboard, admin, operator) this is acceptable — SEO is irrelevant.

For **public indexed routes**, call `notFound()` before any `await` or Suspense to preserve true 404 semantics.

