## `RouteEnvelope` — server-to-client surface context

`RouteEnvelope` (`lib/route-envelope.shared.ts`) is the typed contract for what a layout resolves after session and org authority. It bridges server-resolved context to client-side `error.tsx` boundaries via `RouteEnvelopeProvider` (`components/route-envelope-context.tsx`).

```ts
export type RouteSurface =
  | "locale"
  | "dashboard"
  | "admin"
  | "operator"
  | "auth"
  | "iam"
  | "account"
  | "console"
  | "org"
export interface RouteEnvelope { surface: RouteSurface; locale: string; orgSlug?: string; orgId?: string }
```

Usage in `error.tsx`:
```tsx
const envelope = useRouteEnvelope()
const segment = envelope?.orgSlug ? `dashboard/${envelope.orgSlug}` : "dashboard"
useReportRouteError({ segment, error })
```

### RouteEnvelope — evolution path

Today: `{ surface, locale, orgSlug?, orgId? }`.

**Add fields only when a concrete consumer ships.** Do not speculate.

| Field       | Add when                                                                                              |
| ----------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `module?`   | Per-module page wrappers exist that need to include module name in error reports without parsing URLs |
| `traceId?`  | OpenTelemetry instrumentation lands; layouts broadcast active trace to client error boundaries        |
| `actorId?`  | Sentry user scoping needs the actor client-side (already available server-side on the session)        |

