## `metadata` in layouts

Use `export const metadata: Metadata` when the title is fixed (most layouts).

Use `export async function generateMetadata({ params })` when the title needs dynamic data — e.g. org name in the browser tab:

```tsx
export async function generateMetadata({
  params,
}: LayoutProps<"/[locale]/o/[orgSlug]/dashboard">): Promise<Metadata> {
  const { orgSlug } = await params
  const identity = await fetchOrgWorkbenchIdentity(/* orgId from session */)
  return {
    title: identity?.name ?? orgSlug,
    openGraph: { title: `${identity?.name ?? orgSlug} | ${SITE_NAME}` },
  }
}
```

Fetch requests inside `generateMetadata` are automatically memoized — the same fetch in the layout function is not re-fetched (React `cache` semantics).

---

## Observability and data contracts

- Layouts are the **only place** to emit `logUnexpectedServerError` for layout-level fetch failures. Do not log expected `null` / `notFound()` outcomes.
- Pass minimal, serializable data across the server→client boundary. `RouteEnvelope` carries identifiers only — never full records or session payloads.
- Do not put domain data fetches (contacts list, knowledge chunks, etc.) in `layout.tsx`. Those belong in `page.tsx` or `loading.tsx`-wrapped Server Component leaves.

---

## Relationship to `error-boundaries.mdc`

This rule governs the full five-file surface. The `error.tsx` slot defers to `error-boundaries.mdc` for the approved-boundary allowlist and decision rules.
